The paper presents a fast algorithm for constructing hierarchical nets in finite metric spaces with constant doubling dimension, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also applies the constructed data structure to solve several problems related to approximation algorithms, compression, and analysis of functions, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
